  body
    div(class='container')
      h1 Timestamp Microservice API
      
      blockquote(class='blockquote')
        | User stories:
        ul 1) I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
        ul 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
        ul 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
      
      h3 Example usage:
      code
        a(href='https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/December%2015,%202015') https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/December%2015,%202015
      br
      code
        a(href='https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/1450137600') https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/1450137600
      p
      h3 Example output:
      code
        | { "unix": 1450137600, "natural": "December 15, 2015" }
